            <h2>FAQs</h2>
            <h3>What is the size and layout of Newark Liberty International Airport?</h3>
            <p>The airport covers 2,027 acres (820 ha) and features three runways and one helipad.</p>
            <h3>What are the dimensions of the runways at Newark Liberty International Airport?</h3>
            <p>- Runway 4L/22R: 11,000 ft × 150 ft (3,353 m × 46 m)</p>
            <p>- Runway 4R/22L: 10,000 ft × 150 ft (3,048 m × 46 m)</p>
            <p>- Runway 11/29: 6,726 ft × 150 ft (2,050 m × 46 m)</p>
            <p>- Helipad H1: 54 ft × 54 ft (16 m × 16 m)</p>
            <h3>What kind of improvements have been made to the runways?</h3>
            <p>The Port Authority completed a $97 million rehabilitation project on Runway 4L/22R in 2014 and added four new taxiways to reduce delays.</p>
            <h3>Are the runways equipped for various landing approaches?</h3>
            <p>Yes, all approaches except Runway 29 have Instrument Landing Systems. Runway 4R is certified for Category III approaches.</p>
            <h3>How are the runways used at Newark Liberty International Airport?</h3>
            <p>Runway 4L/22R is primarily used for takeoffs, 4R/22L for landings, and 11/29 is used for smaller aircraft or during strong crosswinds.</p>
            <h3>What taxiway facilities does Newark Liberty International Airport have?</h3>
            <p>The airport features more than 12 miles of 75-foot-wide taxiways, including new taxiways that allow multiple planes to stage for departure and enable faster runway exits for arriving planes.</p>
            <h3>Is there a helipad at Newark Liberty International Airport?</h3>
            <p>Yes, Helipad H1 is used by Blade, a helicopter service providing quick transfers to EWR and JFK.</p>
            <h3>How does Newark Liberty International Airport's layout compare to other major New York-area airports?</h3>
            <p>Unlike JFK and LaGuardia, which are next to large bodies of water, Newark's runways are completely land-locked, situated just across Interstate 95 from Newark Bay.</p>





